<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-B9BF590D-771F-4765-A31E-2131E70CDEB9" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-B9BF590D-771F-4765-A31E-2131E70CDEB9" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">15 The function of media step control </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">This document gives an explanation of the media step control function. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="SECTION_D2E643F57A164045A789311A15694B04" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">General</title><p class="- topic/p ">The media step control is influenced by: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Engine and Media calibrations. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">RIP application settings 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Automatic Advance Correction (AAC) in the media profile (in Media Manager) of the application (e.g Onyx). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">3 options with markers are available: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Off</b> : No correction of the media step control with markers is possible. Reason: the surface of the media is too rough to measure the markers. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b>: Yellow markers are printed at the left and right hand side of the image on the media. A correction of the media step control is possible. This is the most optimal setting for a correct media step control. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Enhanced</b>: 2 x 2 black markers are printed beside the image on the media. This option can be used if the yellow markers can not be read. (Error code 05713 Cannot read markers for media step control). 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">- (Manual) Step Correction 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- Vacuum strength of print surface (platen) fan strengths over the 5 zones (A, B, C, D and E). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Media properties: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- surface 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">- and / or skew (on core) of the media 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-3E53DEB3-C393-4401-B9FA-BFA3DE817036" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Automatic Advance Correction (AAC): Normal = Yellow markers</title><table id="GUID-B0870016-177A-4A8B-9A45-0B4BB5AFC460" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="45*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="45*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Additional information 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 Marker is printed, in yellow, beside the image area at the left and right hand side. 
</p><fig id="GUID-C966AD79-B227-4A94-B892-53A918E7415B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Overview: yellow marker nearly not visible.</title><image href="GUID-A6E82F7A-F896-4ACD-A78A-FC387575F953-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A6E82F7A-F896-4ACD-A78A-FC387575F953-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The media is moved forward. It advances 1 step. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Another yellow marker is printed next to the 1<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">st 
</sup>marker at the left and right hand side. 
</p><fig id="GUID-2416EE92-D543-4705-8571-A97EF4732C64" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Detail left hand side: 2 markers in yellow</title><image href="GUID-8F399098-17AE-4EAA-88E8-125548D6781B-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8F399098-17AE-4EAA-88E8-125548D6781B-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Scan with the M&amp;C unit the markers and calculate the actual media step. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is used as a result to influence future media steps. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-16EE7413-5A7A-4A8D-B6C0-BA47A12E2F90" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Automatic Advance Correction (AAC): Enhanced = Black markers</title><table id="GUID-A61B9BE4-8B6F-4F93-974F-474340754713" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="45*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="45*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Additional information 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 Marker are is printed, in black, beside the image area at the left and right hand side. 
</p><fig id="GUID-B60C20C5-26AE-4DAF-ACE6-23AF21648F0B" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Overview: black markers</title><image href="GUID-FB129745-089D-475B-993E-03FF7E963641-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FB129745-089D-475B-993E-03FF7E963641-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The media is moved forward. It advances 1 step. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" namest="col2" nameend="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Another 2 markers are printed next to the 1<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">st 
</sup>set of 2 markers. 
</p><fig id="GUID-92E15309-1966-43F7-9733-60C7A4A9495E" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Detail left hand side: 2 x 2 markers</title><image href="GUID-7C574AAA-EF10-4FED-A1CC-14A72A5151D0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C574AAA-EF10-4FED-A1CC-14A72A5151D0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Scan with the M&amp;C unit, the markers and calculate the actual media step. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use the result to influence future media steps. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-56142F1B-D3A1-46E9-910C-EEE3067DB3E1.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
